Sheet metal paint is available in both spray paint and brush-on options. Both types of paint work well for home decorating purposes. Choose a brush or roller size appropriate for your sheet metal project. If the sheet metal is large, select a wide brush or roller; if the sheet metal is small, choose a smaller brush or roller. For best paint control, hold the brush at the base of the handle near the bristles. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Apply 2 coats of the paint, allowing the first coat to dry completely before applying the second coat. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7c/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7c/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-6Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/68/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/68/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet1-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet1-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Test the nozzle before applying paint to the sheet metal. Spray a small amount of paint on a newspaper or piece of cardboard to ensure the nozzle is working correctly and sprays paint evenly. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/09/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/09/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet2-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet2-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Apply spray paint to the sheet metal. Hold the spray paint can 12 to 24 inches (30.4 to 60.9 cm) from the surface. Spray in a quick, smooth and even pattern until the surface is covered. For best results, keep the can parallel to the sheet metal surface and spray in a back and forth motion over the surface. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet3-Version-2.jpg/v4-460px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet3-Version-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e2/Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet3-Version-2.jpg/v4-760px-Paint-Sheet-Metal-for-Home-Decorating-Step-7Bullet3-Version-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
